# Custom Domains Module

## Architecture

Tenant custom domains are managed through Vercel's Domains API with a DLQ pattern for resilience.

## Domain status lifecycle

```
pending_dns -> verifying -> active
                         -> conflict (misconfigured DNS)
                         -> error (Vercel API failure)
           -> deleted (soft delete)
```

## Auth and governance (required before every mutation)

1. `requireRequestUser` — session auth
2. `assertTenantAccess` — role check (editor for reads, admin for mutations)
3. `assertDomainGovernance` — plan/feature gate
4. `assertDomainPolicy` — domain format validation (POST only)
5. `enforceDomainMutationRateLimit` — rate limit (POST/DELETE only)

## DLQ pattern

Failed Vercel operations are enqueued to `tenant_domain_dlq`:
- Automatic retry via `POST /api/v1/internal/domains/reconcile` (cron)
- Manual retry via `POST /api/v1/internal/domains/dlq/:id/retry` (admin)
- DLQ items track `attempts`, `last_error_code`, `next_retry_at`

## Supabase tables

- `tenant_domains` — domain records with status, verification targets, Vercel payload
- `tenant_domain_events` — audit trail (all add/remove/verify/status operations)
- `tenant_domain_dlq` — dead letter queue for failed Vercel operations

## Idempotency

POST (add) and DELETE (remove) support `Idempotency-Key` header. Replay check via `tenant_domain_events`.

## Metrics and telemetry

- `domain_add_success/error`, `domain_remove_success/error`, `domain_verify_success/error`, `domain_status_refresh_success/error`, `domain_list_success`
- Structured logs via `logDomain(severity, event, context)`
